snippet: A successful completion of an austerity program would be a significant psychological threshold for the 17-nation euro zone.
abstract: Irish Prime Min Enda Kenny declares imminent end of economic crisis, predicting that country will emerge from international bailout program in December; if timetable holds, Ireland will be first of four countries that received bailouts to end dependence on international support.
lead_paragraph: A successful completion of an austerity program would be a significant psychological threshold for the 17-nation euro zone.

headline.main: Setting Pace, Ireland Predicts December Exit From Bailout
headline.print_headline: Setting Pace, Ireland Predicts December Exit From Bailout
